                <h1 class="section-heading fw-normal">Tourism & Hospitality Activities In Soibada, Timor-Leste</h1>
                <h4 class="section-heading">A. To develop promotional material leading with the historical location of Soibada.</h4>
                <h4 class="section-heading">B. Build and operate the  First Hotel & Shopping Facility in Soibada Timor-Leste.</h4>
                <h4 class="section-heading">C. Develop, Manage and Maintain, in Soibada the National Sanctuary Of The Lady of Aitara.</h4>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">Develop, Manage and Maintain, in Soibada the National Sanctuary Of  The Lady of Aitara  if this project is available, this would see constant supervision and continual maintenance and upgrading of the National Sanctuary so as to bring this facility to international standards and increase its international reputation and to further enhance the promotion of the National Sanctuary.</p>
                <h4 class="section-heading">D. Develop, Manage and Maintain , In Soibada the future facilities of The Mountain Cruz</h4>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.1. Develop a Secure Stair Way with hand rails to the top of the Mountain Cruz and</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.2. Develop resting areas on the way to the top so those less “FIT” or needing to take in a breath or two and do so  with safety.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.3. Each resting area can have secure strong seating and have available some shelter from the sun or rain.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.4. These resting area would make excellent photographic locations that can be talked about each time these travellers mention The Cruz to anyone.  </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.5. The Secure Stair Way to the top would allow visitors to be able to climb at their own pace and view in safety the site of the Cruz, and enjoy the view at each stage of the climb, enjoy the view of the other  mountains on the way up</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.6. Develop a Lift System or a cable car system for the visitors whom are unable to climb any stairs to the top, or for those that just want take photographs “on the way up” or just prefer to enjoy the view from the external of the mountain to anywhere in sight.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.7. Develop  a Viewing Tower and construct a platform to handle approximately 200 people at any one viewing.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.8. Build & maintain & manage suitable bus & car & motorcycle parking facilities, with parking attendants on duty during the active traffic periods & busiest days.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.9. To install under cover picnic facilities , rubbish bins, toilets blocks for males & females.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.10. Install information signage & safety signage.</p>
                <h4>Develop “Park Ranger Services”</h4>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">D.11 The Foundãço Gino Favaro can Develop “Park Ranger Services” and to have security patrols with the ability to help any person in need, to take care of any local wildlife,  develop appropriate fencing and overseeing the security of the Cruz Mountain Religious Tourism site.</p>
                <h4 class="section-heading">E. Natural Water Falls at Soibada Tiris- Maubilik At Desa Leo-Hat.</h4>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">Natural Water Falls “We- Tiris-Baulelo  in Soibada,  Another place of special interest, through donor funding The Fundação Gino Favaro  could oversee the development of Natural Water Falls “We- Tiris-Baulelo , and continue to Manage and maintain This location.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">Natural Water Falls at Soibada Tiris- Maubilik At Desa Leo-Hat, where you can see an image of an ancient persons Face in the Rocks near the top of the water falls and other faces on the rock walls of the water falls.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">To be able to create a safe parking space within the vicinity of the waterfalls, guarded by park rangers, and install all covered picnic facilities near it, such as huts, so all tourists could have a place where they put all their belongings while enjoying the beautiful spots.</p>
                <h4 class="section-heading">F. The Area of Traditional Cooking with Banana Leaves and Bamboo</h4>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">The Area of Traditional Cooking with Banana Leaves and Bamboo plus Eating with hand- made traditional bamboo Plates and Spoons, To develop a road into this area construct car parking and toilets & picnic facilities. A couple of small food canteens for the local so they be more hygienic in the preparation and  presentation of their foods.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">To be able to generate jobs coming from the services made from this area of traditional cooking with banana leaves and bamboo. This action could also help the locals not to forget their own traditions while working in the modern world with the different nationalities of tourists present.</p>
                <h4 class="section-heading">G. Develop  the Mountain Dia</h4>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">With consultation with the local people Foundação Gino Favaro could develop  the Mountain Dia, area so that it is easier to explore the Natural Beauty , observe the local wild animals and to visit the mountain and the view Sealed Holes .</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">Second, to be able to create a safe parking space within the vicinity of the mountain, guarded by park rangers, and install all covered picnic facilities near it, such as huts, so all tourists could have a place where they put all their belongings while enjoying the beautiful spots.</p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">Third, an installation of all rubbish bins and other utilities used for hygiene is also recommended in order to maintain the cleanliness of the environment. Lastly, to generate jobs such as tourist guides in climbing the mountain so the tourists could safely enjoy the activity of climbing Mountain Dia.</p>
                <h4 class="section-heading">H. Help promote and develop the area, car parking ,toilets, a road in to the location of The Spiritual House Keu-Mauk.</h4>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">To be able to create a safe parking space within the vicinity of the Spiritual House, guarded by park rangers, and installation of all rubbish bins and other utilities used for hygiene is also recommended in order to maintain the cleanliness of the environment.</p>
